  "footnotes": [
    "Principality of Arbanon (1190–1216): Considered the first Albanian state; centred around Krujë; founded by Progon; disappeared after Mongol pressure and Byzantine reconquest.",
    "Kingdom of Albania (1272–1285): Established by Charles I of Anjou who claimed the Adriatic coast; the name 'Albania' appears prominently in Western sources from this period.",
    "League of Lezhë (1444): Coalition of Albanian lords led by Gjergj Kastrioti (Skanderbeg) that resisted Ottoman expansion for 25 years until his death (1468) and the fall of Shkodër (1479).",
    "Ali Pasha of Ioannina (1788–1822): Semi-independent Ottoman warlord controlling much of southern Albania and Epirus; his revolt against the Sultan prompted the Greek War of Independence.",
    "Northern Epirus / Vorio Epirus: Southern Albania claimed by Greece, with Greek-majority areas; Autonomous Republic of Northern Epirus declared in 1914, absorbed by Albania after WWI.",
    "K = northeast Kukës · S = Shkodër · D = Durrës · T = central Tirana · V = Vlorë · O = southeast Lake Ohrid (source footnote)"
  ]
